<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><image-reference id="_cea5e216-e321-4e3a-aa64-e1074a35859f"><num>13.2.7a (explanatory)</num><title id="_b9347b96-d6ad-4253-b2d0-712da14b1f76">Attached Class 10a building examples</title><image height="599" heightdpi="200" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/13-2-7-explanatory-attached-class-10a-building-examples.svg" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/><desc-note id="_f345308f-3956-419c-992e-e0188a288288"><p>In (a), the thermal performance <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_c47441a6-dd70-4844-a658-ae33a02ae1e1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> for the Class 1 building may be achieved by including the walls and floor of the Class 1 building that adjoin the Class 10a garage.</p><p>In (b), the thermal performance <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_ef18a80e-54ed-4449-a998-511d9ae964a5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> for the Class 1 building may be achieved by including the outside walls and floor of the Class 10a garage.</p><p>For <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_c90f4b13-7ccd-4bd7-a857-73b32d4abbae" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 4 and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1458_0.16.0.xml#_0d25cef7-0651-40ea-a0e6-3d3db1191e24" id="_1bd76156-1f86-489f-8441-42bec5357ac9" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">climate zone</xref> 5 in Western Australia, 13.2.7(2) provides the minimum insulation to be added to floors where separating between a Class 1 building and a Class 10 building, as shown in (a) of the figure.</p></desc-note></image-reference>